name: thedailybeast
text: When @mattwilstein talked to @JessicaKirson back in March for a piece about how comedians were coping with the pandemic, she said: “It’s very hard to not do stand-up. I’m one of those comics who go up every night...so it’s very hard to not perform.” https://t.co/8om6vd6WSi

name: thedailybeast
text:
On finally getting her "long overdue" stand-up special "Talking To Myself," @JessicaKirson says it may be because she "was never the hot, skinny, flirtatious female comedian."

"I was just funny," she says. https://t.co/YRWpZbmOaY

name: thedailybeast
text: Listen to the full interview on #TheLastLaugh podcast here: https://t.co/YRWpZbmOaY

name: thedailybeast
text:
President Trump asked Sen. Ted Cruz for a big favor this week. In the unlikely case that Texas attorney general’s election fraud lawsuit reaches the Supreme Court, the president wanted to know if Senator Cruz would make the oral arguments. 

Cruz said yes. https://t.co/4GWwkbT3dB

text: A member of a white supremacist and neo-Nazi group has been sentenced for taking part in a plan to “threaten and intimidate journalists and advocates who worked to expose anti-Semitism,” the Department of Justice said  https://t.co/XmFmHJj9fz

name: thedailybeast
text:
SpaceX had a major fail, er, victory on Wednesday.

The aerospace company launched a new rocket from its testing facility in Texas, but after climbing eight miles into the sky, the rocket fell back to earth and exploded. https://t.co/EYJPyD7FzC

name: thedailybeast
text:
An anti-mask mob descended on the home of a county commissioner as she prepared to vote on a mask mandate—while she was at the office and her kids were home alone. 

@MichaelDalyNYC calls her "a true patriot in a time of preposterous imposters." https://t.co/ew7etOGl1i
